-- 56. Formatting Dates and Times

-- In Mysql, the date is in format '2019-01-01', which is not that 
-- user friendly.So, there are some functions to represent dates 
-- in a more user friendly way.

1. DATE_FORMAT():-

-- Used to format dates as per our demand.
-- Takes two parameters, first is tha date and second is the format.

-- Select DATE_FORMAT(NOW(),'%D %M %Y');
-- Result:-12th November 2022.


2. TIME_FORMAT():-

-- Used to represent time in a specific format.

-- Select TIME_FORMAT(NOW(), '%h:%i:%s');
-- Result:-07:38:55.
